Tshwane metro police spokesperson Isaac Mahamba said at least seven injured people were transported to hospital for treatment. JOHANNESBURG - Two people were killed and at least seven others were injured in a car pile-up on the N1 between the Petroport and Walmansthal. Authorities said the accident involved nine cars and two trucks. Tshwane metro police spokesperson Isaac Mahamba said at least seven injured people were transported to the hospital for treatment. “Traffic has been closed on the N1 and is being directed toward the M4. Those who are coming from Polokwane south into the CBD, they have been redirected to Walmansthal.”